text.__SUMMARY__: Conus nanshaensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.This snail is predatory and venomous and is capable of "stinging" humans.
text.Distribution: This marine species of cone snail occurs off the Spratly Islands, the South China Sea.
text.References: Li F.-L. [Fenglan] & Lin M.-Y. [Minyu]. (2016). Fauna Sinica. Invertebrata 55. Mollusca: Gastropoda: Conidae. Beijing: Science Press. 286 pp., 4 pls. page(s): 73, fig. 43
